HEADWORD: Sponger
<hw>Spon"ger</hw> <pr>(-j⟦etil⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>One who sponges, or uses a sponge.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One employed in gathering sponges.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Fig.: A parasitical dependent; a
hanger-on.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

